text.paragraph: Includes: History of Present Illness from this encounter

paragraph.content: Matthew Lewis is a 72 year old female.
Pt presents today to discuss her back pain. She does see PM- Dr. Wei. She was supposed to have a joint injection but accidentally took Aspirin. Pt is trying to see a new doctor- Dr. Baboo in January.
Pt reports lower back pain radiating down her back. She is taking Tramadol BID, PRN. She is requesting a disabled parking permit. Pt uses a roller walker to ambulate.
Pt is requesting scripts for orthopedic scooter, bathtub bar, trapeze.
Pt is also unsure of what medications she is supposed to be on and would like a medication summary.
HTN- Losartan, Amlodipine, Carvedilol, Torsemide (K), Clonidine, PRN
GERD/peptic ulcer- Pantoprazole, Sucralfate, Promethazine, Ondansetron

text.paragraph: Includes: Review of Systems from this encounter

paragraph.content: Systemic: No generalized pain and not feeling tired or poorly. No fever, no chills, and no recent weight change. No night sweats, no edema, and no aching.
Head: No headache, no facial pain, no sinus pain, and no sinus pressure.
Neck: No neck pain, no neck stiffness, no lump or swelling in the neck, and no swollen glands in the neck.
Eyes: No vision problems, no dryness of the eyes, and no itching of the eyes. No pain in or around the eyes, no discharge from the eyes, and no photophobia.

Otolaryngeal: No hearing loss, no earache, the ears do not feel full, no discharge from the ears, no tinnitus, no nasal discharge, no postnasal drip, no epistaxis, no nasal itching, no hoarseness, no sore throat, no choking, no teeth symptoms, gums normal, and no jaw pain.
Cardiovascular: No chest pain or discomfort, no palpitations, the heart rate was not slow, the heart rate was not fast, no intermittent leg claudication, no cold hands or feet, and no varicose veins.
Pulmonary: Not feeling congested in the chest, no dyspnea, no orthopnea, no cough, no hemoptysis, and no wheezing.
Gastrointestinal: Normal appetite, no dysphagia, no heartburn, and no regurgitation. No nausea, no vomiting, no bloating, and no abdominal pain. No flatus, no diarrhea, and no constipation.
Genitourinary: No hematuria, no changes in urinary habits, no urinary loss of control, no dysuria, and no pain in the flank. No genital lesion and no bowel/bladder changes.
Endocrine: No polydipsia, no temperature intolerance, no excessive sweating, no feeling weak, no sexual complaints, and no hair symptoms.
Musculoskeletal: No back pain, no pain in the pelvic girdle, no muscle aches, no muscle cramps, no muscle spasms, no localized joint pain, and no localized joint stiffness.

Neurological: No dizziness, no vertigo, no lightheadedness, no fainting, no confusion, no memory lapses or loss, no taste disturbances, no speech difficulties, no motor disturbances, no difficulty with balance, and no sensory disturbances.
Psychological: No anxiety, no depression, no sleep disturbances, and a desire to continue living. No homicidal thoughts, no emotional problems/concerns, and no interpersonal relationship problems.
Skin: No dry skin, no pruritus, and no change in skin texture. No skin lesions and nails are normal.
